reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2024
reviews.reviewText: My doctor recommended these types of cushions for my back. I purchased two, one for my car seat and one against the back of the car seat to support my back. The cushions are sturdy and heavy. Comfortable to use.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Is not a Gel cushion. Look at photos. It is more like a honeycomb.
reviews.reviewText: I was very disappointed when I unpacked this thing. I use a lift chair and with just me sitting in it in the same spot all the time the cushion has become very uncomfortable. I also sleep in the chair so comfort matters. I remembered how comfortable the gel cushion my mother had was, and that is what I thought I was buying. I looked at this and decided to try it. It is not thick and it is not gel, but it does seem to cushion the seat in my chair so that I am comfortable again. I keep a towel wrapped around it, and I pick it up and flip it over and around frequently. It is not heavy. It is two layers of honeycombed flexible plastic. I'm not sure how or why it works but it does seem to work well.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 27, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Man this cushion is ridiculously soft and it keeps your bottom cool. I drive Passenger busses for a living and after having to sit in that seat for hours at a time on long routes if I didn't have this I would've quit. And easy to clean and it does not attract smells. Not that your bum should be smelling anyway 🤣
